Planet Runa

Basic Information

  • Name: Runa
  • Other Names/Aliases: (e.g., local names, ancient names)
  • Classification: Garden World, Toxic Atmosphere
  • System and Location: HV 2112, Small Magellanic Cloud
  • NavCords: 58042.86, 18318.75, 194394.29
  • Population: 7.32 billion (5.7b Runi, 1.62b Niandr, > 0.01 Human)
  • Controlled By: Pre-Starfaring Culture Protection Services (PSCPS), and a multitude of local governments.

Physical Characteristics

  • Diameter: 10,204.8 km
  • Gravity: 1.77 g
  • Atmosphere Composition: Nitrogen: 70.79%, Oxygen: 24.31%, and 4.90% Other
  • Day Length: 19 hours
  • Year Length: 2,325.07 Earth Days
  • Moons: 3
    • Teli: 0.89 Lunar masses
    • Meti: 1.18 Lunar masses
    • Vei: 0.42 Lunar masses
  • Surface Features: Massive sprawling forests, extremely high mountain ranges.
  • Climate: Predominantly temperate, the tropical zone is very narrow and the poles are likewise small. 68% of the planet's surface is located within temperate regions.
  • Notable Natural Phenomena: Thermal Years. Runa's star fluctuates in brightness due to contamination of its fusion mass. This takes the form of a notable dimming of the star occurring in a cycle of roughly 600 Earth days. This leads to the Runi concept of a year, which is one full dimming cycle from the start of one period of full brightness to the next.

The planet Runa is a unique world located in the Small Magellanic Cloud. It is he first planet in orbit of HV 2112, an unusual star best known for its 600 day long dimming cycle. Runa's life is adapted to the cycle, with both sapients inhabiting the planet using the time from the start of one bright acle to the next as their equivalent to a year.

Runa was once far more alien than it is now. 2000 years ago a terraforming accident radically altered Runa's ecosphere, leading to it becoming a near-Earth world, and the creation of the Runi species. Despite the catastrophy plenty of the old world's features survive. Including the keystone of Runa's biosphere, its plethora of crystal outcroppings.

Old Runa Biosphere

Runa has an absurd abundance of silica crystals t.ae to a significant percentage of its ecosphere being based on microbes which utilize biomineralization as a major part of their life cycle. This in turn led to a world were evolving life often integrated crystals with their" biology in one or more ways. This includes plant life, which on Runa often makes use of photovoltaic crystal for photosynthesis and can undergo bio mineralization, producing the planets many stunning above ground crystal outcroppings in a manner similar to coral.

Animal life also makes use of crystal on Runa. Often in unexpectedly unique ways. Many animals eyes use crystals for lenses (While common in pre-history on many worlds, Runa's fauna has evolved the concept to advanced camera-like states.), some use photovoltaics as a food supplement, others even use photonic systems in small parts of their brains. The integration of crystals is so, complete that they are best categorized as a dule carbon-silica based life form.

Dimming Cycles

Runa's sun is famous for its Diming Cycles. These are genuine change in apparent magnitude which occur when material ingested by a now dead companion star "connects" to the surface. The total time between peek brightness is 600+/-15 earth days. Runa's sapient species use these cycles in place of orbits to track time.

While Runa has seasons they make a minimal impact on the ecosphere compared to the Dimming Cycle. When its sun is at full brightness Runa's temperature averages 19C globally. During the dimmest period the global average falls to 13 C. All plant and animal life is adapted not only to this 6 degree temperature flux, but also the 0.00012% change in solar energy availability.

Runa Durring a Cold Piriod

Seasons

Runa has seasons like any other planet with a notable axial tilt. There are the usual four seasons-spring, summer, all, and winter-but these compound with the Dimming Cycle and are complicated by Runa's three moons. Runa's orbital period is 2,325.07 Earth days long. Its seasons would be years long by earth standards if not for the gravitational influence of its moons, which induce a mild" wobble" of the planets axial tilt. This lunar wobble. causes a regular seasonal cycle of 5.3 months +1-8 days Earth time).

The dimming cycle does not align with the seasons. This creates a procession of" Hot"," Warm", and" Cold" versions of the seasons.

  • Warm seasons are what might be thought of as normal for a season. They occur when a season occurs while the sun is brightening and also when it if dimming.
  • Hot seasons are extreme temperature versions of the seasons. They are usually wet as evaporation increases, and are so warm that a Hot winter can be the same as a Cold Summer.
  • Cold seasons are extreme weather laden colder versions of the seasons. They are capable of making a summer feel like early winter.

Inhabitants

Runi is home to two sapient species, the Niandr and the Runi. The niandr are the original native species, having naturally evolved on Runa in ancient times. The Runi are the result of a terraforming accident, but no less native to Runa than the niandr.

Both species exist primarily side by side but with the niandr ignoring the Runi most of the time due to their species peculiar nature. The Runi are seemingly happy to oblige the niandr in some areas, but in others they take measures to be independent, isolated as the situation permits, and secure. This attitude is due to the niandr having treated the runi as animals to manage in some well known historic and even recent cases. This has complicated Terran efforts to guide both species towards the stars. The niandr are apathetic towards out groups while the Runi are suspicious of them.
